# 🚀 Ponder Sepolia Event Indexer

A blockchain event indexing project built with **Ponder**, **Solidity**, **GraphQL**, and **JavaScript**.

This project demonstrates how to index smart contract events deployed on the Sepolia testnet and expose them through a GraphQL API with a simple frontend dashboard.

---

## 📌 Features

- Smart contract deployed on Sepolia
- Event indexing using Ponder
- GraphQL API for querying indexed data
- Responsive frontend dashboard
- Search indexed messages
- Track Created, Updated, and Deleted events
- Real-time indexing during development

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- Solidity
- Ponder
- GraphQL
- TypeScript
- JavaScript
- HTML & CSS
- Sepolia Testnet
- Alchemy RPC

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
.
├── abis/                 # Smart contract ABI
├── frontend/             # HTML/CSS/JS dashboard
├── generated/            # Auto-generated Ponder files
├── src/                  # Event handlers
├── ponder.config.ts      # Ponder configuration
├── ponder.schema.ts      # Database schema
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

---

## 📦 Installation

Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<username>/ponder-sepolia-indexer.git

cd ponder-sepolia-indexer
```

Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

---

## ⚙ Environment Variables

Create a `.env.local` file.

```env
PONDER_RPC_URL_1=https://eth-sepolia.g.alchemy.com/v2/YOUR_API_KEY
```

---

## ▶ Start the Project

Run the Ponder indexer

```bash
npm run dev
```

Ponder will start

- GraphQL Server
- Database
- Event Indexer

GraphQL Playground

```
http://localhost:42069/graphql
```

---

## 🔎 Sample GraphQL Query

```graphql
{
  messagess(limit: 10) {
    items {
      id
      author
      content
      timestamp
      exists
    }
  }
}
```

